<p><i><b>Nobilis</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Contemporary_fantasy" title="Contemporary fantasy">contemporary fantasy</a> <a href="/wiki/Role-playing_game" title="Role-playing game">role-playing game</a> created by <a href="/wiki/R._Sean_Borgstrom" title="R. Sean Borgstrom" class="mw-redirect">R. Sean Borgstrom</a>. The <a href="/wiki/Player_characters" title="Player characters" class="mw-redirect">player characters</a> are "Sovereign Powers" called <i>the Nobilis</i>; each Noble is the <a href="/wiki/Personification" title="Personification">personification</a> of an abstract concept or class of things such as Time, Death, cars, or communication. Unlike most role-playing games, <i>Nobilis</i> <a href="/wiki/Diceless_role-playing_game" title="Diceless role-playing game">does not use dice</a> or other random elements to determine the outcome of characters' actions, but instead uses a Karma-based system for task resolution.</p>
